===========================================================================

  Paley: S = [1, 2, 4], H = 189
    Cycle counts: {3: 14, 5: 42, 7: 24}
    α_0 =      1  (2^0·α_0 =      1)
    α_1 =     80  (2^1·α_1 =    160)
    α_2 =      7  (2^2·α_2 =     28)
    I(Ω, 2) = 189

  Interval: S = [1, 2, 3], H = 175
    Cycle counts: {3: 14, 5: 28, 7: 17}
    α_0 =      1  (2^0·α_0 =      1)
    α_1 =     59  (2^1·α_1 =    118)
    α_2 =     14  (2^2·α_2 =     56)
    I(Ω, 2) = 175

  KEY INSIGHT at p=7:
  Paley wins via α_1: 80*2 = 160 vs 59*2 = 118  (Δ = +42)
  Interval wins via α_2: 7*4 = 28 vs 14*4 = 56   (Δ = -28)
  Net: Paley +42-28 = +14 = 189-175 ✓

  Paley has MORE total odd cycles (80 vs 59)
  but FEWER independent pairs (7 vs 14)
  Why? Paley cycles overlap MORE — the 'random' connectivity
  of QR creates dense overlap in the cycle graph.
  Interval cycles, being 'local' (small steps), overlap LESS.

